# Aurora — frontend environment variables.
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values. NEVER commit `.env`.
#
# Both vars are PUBLIC (the anon key is safe in the browser — Row Level
# Security protects the data; see plan.md §6). The Supabase service_role key
# must NEVER appear here or anywhere in the frontend.
#
# Find these in your Supabase dashboard: Settings → API.

# Your Supabase project URL, e.g. https://abcdefgh.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=

# Your Supabase public anon key (starts with "eyJ...")
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# That's all the frontend needs. Two server-side features use secrets that live
# ONLY in the Supabase dashboard (Edge Function secrets) — they are NOT VITE_
# vars and must NEVER be added here or shipped to the browser:
#   - EMAIL REMINDERS: RESEND_API_KEY, REMINDER_FROM_EMAIL, CRON_SECRET
#     (setup: supabase/README.md -> "Due-date email reminders").
#   - DODO PAYMENTS BILLING: DODO_PAYMENTS_API_KEY, DODO_WEBHOOK_SECRET,
#     DODO_PRODUCT_PRO_MONTHLY, DODO_PRODUCT_PRO_ANNUAL, APP_URL (and optional
#     DODO_PAYMENTS_ENVIRONMENT=test|live) — setup: supabase/README.md ->
#     "Dodo Payments billing". (Dodo replaced Stripe; it's a Merchant of Record
#     that also handles sales tax / VAT.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
